{
  "doc_id": "29444",
  "text": "Work-family conflict: Work-family conflict was measured using two subscales (5 items for WFC and 5 items for FWC) and included ten items developed by [CITATION_1] . The Cronbach alpha reported 0.77. Well-being: In this research major components of well-being are considered: job satisfaction, family satisfaction and life satisfaction. Family Satisfaction was measured using 3 items developed by [CITATION_2] , the Cronbach alpha reported 0.68; Job satisfaction was measured using 5 items developed by Hachman and Oldham (1975) ; the Cronbach alpha reported 0.83; and life satisfaction was measured using 5 items developed by Diener",
